Package strategy

Description

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Board
    This interface describes the only behavior that a client can assume when a game is created by calling the appropriate factory method, makeGame() in the StrategyGameFactory.
    Piece
    This interface describes the basic behavior required for the Strategy piece.
    StrategyGame
    This is the main class for the Strategy game.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Board.SquareType
    This enumeration identifies the type of square, or the terrain, that the square has on the board.
    Piece.PieceColor
    Enaumeration of the two sides, identified by their color.
    Piece.PieceType
    Enumeration of piece types.
    StrategyGame.MoveResult
    The possible results that will be returned from the move() method.
    StrategyGame.Version
    Enumeration of game versions.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    NotImplementedException
    Exception used in default methods of interfaces
    StrategyException
    A runtime exception that is used in the Strategy game.
